student_data.notes: Data represents the College of Computing enrollment for Fall 2023. The Master's count (16,843) is exceptionally high because it includes the Online Master of Science in Computer Science (OMSCS) program. On-campus MS enrollment is significantly lower (approx 500-1000 typically), but the official facts page aggregates them. [WARNING: Original source was inaccessible, using fallback.]

gpu_resources.notes: GPU counts reflect the new 'AI Makerspace' dedicated student cluster (160 H100s) announced April 2024. The university's central research computing (PACE) clusters 'Phoenix' and 'Hive' contain additional V100, A100, and RTX resources, but exact inventory counts are not publicly enumerated in documentation, only queue names are listed. Therefore, PACE resources are marked as -1 (present but uncounted) to avoid undercounting. [WARNING: Original source was inaccessible, using fallback.]

analysis_notes: Georgia Tech presents a unique data profile: A massive confirmed H100 deployment (160 GPUs) specifically for students via the AI Makerspace, and a very large Master's enrollment due to the OMSCS program. Research cluster counts (PACE) are opaque regarding specific quantities.
